cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS 

The paper focuses on information retrieval and discovering surprising information in textual datasets, which suggests it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a margin-based online learning algorithm, which is commonly used in machine learning and falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with hyperlinked document corpora, which could fall under the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of categories to model the hyperlinks graph could also be related to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with processing large amounts of data efficiently, which could be related to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
